snippet.textDisplay: Brad I need your help 😭 I wish I recorded my hair lightening process. I bleached my natural hair and I didn’t do much with it besides bleach and tone and my hair was down to my back. I then decided I wanted to get a balayage at a salon. My ends were bleach blonde and I would say my roots were like a level 5. I decided to use a box dye and just have it all dark. My box dye faded out to like a honey brown but the places where my hairdresser touched were still just as dark. I ended up cutting my hair shoulder length and decided to go blonde again. I used color remover and bleach and I spaced out sessions every other week and I have been babying my hair in between sessions. I have orange banding all over the mid shaft of my hair and it’s just not lifting AT ALL.

snippet.textDisplay: Betanin, found in beet juice, is a light pink dye. It is used to dye things like strawberry yogurt and has a low shelf life, meaning it fades drastically after about 48 hours. It’s been over a years since I did red dye research, but using beets as a hair dye makes absolutely no sense to me.
